    "comment": "Rationale: Using a PKC beta specific antibody and knockout control, it is demonstrated that PKC beta is expressed at the presynaptic terminal of the calyx of held.\n\n10/3/2017 Pim:\n-Literal: \"In slices from wild-type mice, antibody labeling for PKCα and PKCβ overlapped with vGlut1 labeling, consistent with presynaptic localization of these kinases at the calyx of Held synapse.\"\n-PCKalpha has C2 domain and is able to interact with lipids membranes. In previous annotations of this expert it was established that only a small fraction of the total PKC pool is membrane attached; the rest resides in the cytoplasm. Therefore, the \"cytosol\" component of the term is inferred. Because domain information is not reflected in GO, I agreed to this term.. Experimental description: In slices from wild-type mice, antibody labeling for PKCα and PKCβ overlapped with vGlut1 labeling, consistent with presynaptic localization of these kinases at the calyx of Held synapse.",
